Common Text Transformation Library

Version 3.02
Dec 6 2012

Release Notes

----------
BUG FIXES
----------
Compatibility issues with MSVC++2010 and GCC-4.7.2 got resolved.
Only a few minor changes. CTTL version 3.02 is fully tested with

g++ (GCC) (Ubuntu/Linaro 4.7.2-2ubuntu1) 4.7.2 (64 bit)
g++ (GCC) 4.6.1 (MinGW-3.20 32 bit)
g++ (GCC) 4.3.0 20080305 (alpha-testing) mingw-20080502
MSVC 2010 Version 16.00.40219.01 for 80x86 (32 bit)
MSVC 8.0 Version 14.00.50727.762 (2005)
MSVC 7.1 Version 13.10.3077 (2003)




Version 3.0
Aug 16 2009

Release Notes

1. Input class (centralized substring state) is no longer part of the library.
2. Substring classes re-implemented to support distributed state.
3. Major documentation overhaul.
4. Multiple 64-bit compatibility updates.
5. Sample code updates.
6. Small bug fixes.



Version 3.01

Aug 22 2009

Release Notes

1.  New features:
    begin(R) - positive lookahead assertion added:
        cttl/xtl_metaphor.h
        cttl/xtl_op_impl.h
        cttl/policy.h

2.  Bug fixes:
        example/cpp_comment.h - bug fixed to exclude newline at the tail of //comment.
        lambda/xst_edge_translator.h - version update

3.  New and revised sample programs:
        example/lambda/syntax/node_edge/node_token_boundary.cpp - new lambda sample added.
        example/lambda/misc/balanced_output.cpp - code revision and documentation update.
        example/lambda/xml/xml_lexer.h - a few code revisions.


